55, The lex Cornelia de sicariis et veneficis (Dig. 48. 5) was passed by Sulla in the first or second year of his dictatorship, circ. 81 tae The charge on which Roscius Amerinus was defended by Cicero was based upon its provisions. Its penalties were aquae et ignis interdictio, to which Julius Caesar added forfaiture, Dig. 48. 8. 3. 5, but in many cases death was inflicted; ‘sed solent hodie capite puniri, nisi honestiore loco positi fuerint, ut poenam legis sustineant’ Dig. loc cit.
